# KMP coding standards

- Follow `delivery-workflow.mdc` for plan → implement → test → review on every change.
- Prioritize `expect`/`actual` only when no multiplatform library exists.
- Use `kotlinx-coroutines` for concurrency; never use platform-specific threads.
- For UI, use `org.jetbrains.compose` (Compose Multiplatform).
- For resources, use the Compose `Res` API (`Res.string.*`, `Res.drawable.*`), not platform-specific IDs.
- Navigation: Voyager screens/routes in `presentation/navigation/`; keep screen composables thin.
